{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01TADutJuxJT9MUCW3AnNehV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01MoHymbZTKYCpC2WdEjNt1h","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Golonka.generated.22.txt","content":"Golonka\nRoasted Pork Knuckle\n\nIngredients:\n- 2 pork knuckles (about 3-4 lbs each)\n- 2 tablespoons caraway seeds\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons Dijon mustard\n- 2 tablespoons honey\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon paprika\n- 1 teaspoon marjoram\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 cups beef or pork stock\n- 2 cups root vegetables (carrots, parsnips, onions)\n- 2 bay leaves\n- 1 tablespoon cornstarch\n- 3 tablespoons water\n\nInstructions:\n\nPreparation:\nScore the skin of pork knuckles in crosshatch pattern.\nPat dry with paper towels.\n\nMarinade:\nCombine mustard, honey, soy sauce, paprika, marjoram in bowl.\nMix in minced garlic and caraway seeds.\nRub mixture all over knuckles.\nSeason generously with salt and pepper.\nLet marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes.\n\nRoasting:\nPreheat oven to 325°F.\nPlace knuckles in roasting pan skin side up.\nPour stock around the meat.\nScatter vegetables around pan.\nAdd bay leaves.\nRoast for 2.5 to 3 hours, basting every 30 minutes.\nInternal temperature should reach 165°F.\n\nSauce:\nRemove knuckles and vegetables from pan.\nSkim fat from pan juices.\nMix cornstarch with water.\nHeat pan juices on stovetop, whisk in cornstarch slurry.\nSimmer 2-3 minutes until thickened.\nStrain and serve with meat.\n\nServing: Slice meat thinly, serve with pan sauce and vegetables.\n\nServes: 6-8 people\nPrep time: 20 minutes\nCooking time: 3 hours"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":89758,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_i