 and oil.\nMix wet and dry ingredients until dough forms.\nKnead 8-10 minutes until smooth and elastic.\nPlace in oiled bowl, cover, let rise 90 minutes until doubled.\nShape into round loaf on parchment paper.\nBrush top lightly with water.\nPress additional sunflower seeds onto top surface.\nCover and let proof 60 minutes.\nScore top with knife.\nBake at 450°F for 35-40 minutes until crust is dark brown.\nCool completely on wire rack before slicing.\n\nBoth breads:\nPrep time: 20 minutes\nRising time: 150 minutes\nBaking time: 40 minutes\nEach makes: 1 loaf\n\nStorage: Keep in paper bag at room temperature up to 3 days.\nFreeze wrapped loaves up to 3 months.","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
