{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01TADutJuxJT9MUCW3AnNehV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GgbueSUuZKjYtTDnprY1iQ","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/PORK CHOPS WITH APPLES : PORK CHOPS WITH MUSHROOM SAUCE.generated.22.txt","content":"PORK CHOPS WITH APPLES : PORK CHOPS WITH MUSHROOM SAUCE\n\nMAIN RECIPE: PORK CHOPS WITH APPLES\n\nIngredients:\n- 4 thick-cut pork chops (about 1.5 inches)\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 tablespoons butter\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 1 large onion, sliced\n- 3 tart apples (Granny Smith), cored and sliced\n- 1/2 cup apple cider or white wine\n- 1/4 cup chicken stock\n- 1 tablespoon Dijon mustard\n- 1 teaspoon fresh thyme\n- 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon\n\nInstructions for Apple Version:\nPat pork chops dry, season generously with salt and pepper.\nHeat butter and oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.\nSear pork chops 4-5 minutes per side until golden.\nTransfer to plate and set aside.\nIn same skillet, sauté onion 3 minutes until softened.\nAdd apple slices and cook 2 minutes.\nPour in cider and stock, scraping up browned bits.\nStir in mustard, thyme, and cinnamon.\nReturn pork chops to skillet.\nCover and simmer 10-12 minutes until pork reaches 145°F.\nRemove from heat, season with salt and pepper.\n\nServe hot with apple-onion mixture spooned over chops.\n\n---\n\nVARIATION: PORK CHOPS WITH MUSHROOM SAUCE\n\nIngredients:\n- 4 thick-cut pork chops\n- Salt and pepper\n- 2 tablespoons butter\n- 2 tablespoons olive oil\n- 8 oz mushrooms, sliced (cremini, shiitake, or mixed)\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- 1/2 cup beef or chicken stock\n- 1/4 cup sour cream or heavy cream\n- 2 tablespoons Dijon mustard\n- 1 tablespoon fresh parsley\n- 1 teaspoon fresh marjoram\n\nInstructions for Mushroom Version:\nPat pork chops dry and season with salt and pepper.\nHeat butter and oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.\nSear pork chops 4-5 minutes per side until browned.\nRemove and set aside on plate.\nAdd sliced mushrooms to same skillet, sauté 5 minutes.\nAdd minced garlic, cook 1 minute until fragrant.\nPour in stock, scraping browned bits from pan.\nStir in mustard and sour cream until smooth.\nReturn pork chops to skillet.\nCover and simmer 10-12 minutes until internal temp reaches 145°F.\nSeason with salt and pepper.\nGarnish with fresh parsley and marjoram.\n\nBoth versions:\nPrep time: 15 minutes\nCooking time: 25 minutes\nServes: 4 people\n\nServing suggestion: Serve with egg noodles, mashed potatoes, or steamed vegetables."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":89758,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":89758},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7a96224f-17bb-4724-a834-ccff1a4d9776","uuid":"0558dd47-1495-4fdd-9788-35f1fc559bac"}
