{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01TADutJuxJT9MUCW3AnNehV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Xxwp1qaqnKMSLUBaV1EH2F","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/LEMON CURD : LEMON CURD WITH THYME.generated.22.txt","content":"LEMON CURD : LEMON CURD WITH THYME (VARIATION)\n\nCLASSIC LEMON CURD\n\nIngredients:\n- 6 egg yolks\n- 3/4 cup granulated sugar\n- 1/2 cup fresh lemon juice\n- 2 tablespoons lemon zest\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 6 tablespoons butter, cubed\n- 1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nInstructions for Classic:\nWhisk together egg yolks and sugar in heat-safe bowl.\nAdd lemon juice, zest, and salt.\nSet bowl over pot of simmering water (double boiler).\nWhisk constantly for 12-15 minutes until thickened.\nTemperature should reach 160°F for food safety.\nRemove from heat.\nWhisk in butter cubes one at a time until melted and smooth.\nAdd vanilla extract.\nStrain through fine sieve to remove any cooked egg bits.\nTransfer to sterilized jars.\nCool to room temperature before refrigerating.\n\n---\n\nVARIATION: LEMON CURD WITH THYME\n\nIngredients (same as above, plus):\n- 2 tablespoons fresh thyme leaves (or 1 tablespoon dried)\n- 1/4 teaspoon ground white pepper (optional)\n\nInstructions for Thyme Variation:\nFollow same procedure as classic recipe.\nAfter whisking in butter, add fresh thyme leaves and white pepper.\nLet steep for 2-3 minutes.\nStrain through fine sieve, pressing gently on thyme to extract flavor.\nTransfer to jars and cool.\nThe thyme adds subtle herbal notes that complement the citrus.\n\nStorage:\nRefrigerate up to 4 weeks in airtight jars.\nOr freeze up to 6 months.\n\nUses for Lemon Curd:\n- Spread on toast or English muffins\n- Fill tart shells with cream and berries\n- Swirl into yogurt or whipped cream\n- Pipe into small tarts or pastry shells\n- Layer in parfait with meringue pieces\n- Top vanilla ice cream\n- Mix into pound cake batter\n\nPrep time: 10 minutes\nCooking time: 20 minutes\nCooling time: 30 minutes\nYields: about 1 1/2 cups"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":89758,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":89758},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7a96224f-17bb-4724-a834-ccff1a4d9776","uuid":"66c3fc4d-b775-47c5-9895-b12b978570f3"}
