{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01TADutJuxJT9MUCW3AnNehV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Wopp1eKvzxsD5r8RUasEXc","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Profiteroles.generated.22.txt","content":"PROFITEROLES\nchapter 3 | page 52\n\nChoux pastry ingredients:\n- 1 cup water\n- 1/2 cup butter\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1 cup all-purpose flour\n- 4 eggs\n\nChocolate sauce:\n- 8 oz semisweet chocolate [53], chopped\n- 1/2 cup heavy cream\n- 2 tablespoons butter\n- 1 tablespoon corn syrup\n- 1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nFilling:\n- 2 cups heavy cream\n- 3 tablespoons powdered sugar\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\nDirections for choux paste:\n\nPreheat oven 400°F. Line baking sheet with parchment.\n\nBring water, butter, salt to boil. Remove heat. Stir in flour\nall at once, mixing until paste forms and pulls away from pan sides\n[text smudged]. Cool 5 minutes.\n\nBeat in eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition until\nsmooth and glossy. Batter should be stiff but piping consistency.\n\nTransfer to piping bag fitted with 1/2 inch round tip. Pipe small\nmounds 1 1/2 inches apart on prepared sheet. Bake 25-30 minutes\nuntil puffed and golden brown. Do not open oven during cooking.\n\nCool on wire rack 15 minutes, then cool completely.\n\nChocolate sauce preparation:\n\nPlace chopped chocolate in heatproof bowl. Heat cream and butter\ntogether until steaming. Pour over chocolate, let sit 1 minute.\nWhisk until smooth and glossy. Stir in corn syrup and vanilla.\nKeep warm for serving [54].\n\nAssembly and serving:\n\nWhip cold cream with powdered sugar and vanilla until stiff peaks\nform. Slice cooled profiteroles in half horizontally. Pipe or\nspoon cream into bottom half. Replace top.\n\nStack profiteroles in serving dish. Pour warm chocolate sauce over\ntop, allowing it to drizzle down sides. Serve immediately.\n\nAlternative: Instead of fresh cream, use vanilla ice cream. Pour\nchocolate sauce over warm profiteroles filled with ice cream.\n\nPrep: 30 minutes\nBaking: 30 minutes\nChill: 30 minutes\nTotal time: 90 minutes\nServes: 24-30 profiteroles\n\nNOTE: Profiteroles can be made 1 day ahead. Store in airtight\ncontainer at room temperature. Fill with cream just before serving."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":89758,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":89758},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7a96224f-17bb-4724-a834-ccff1a4d9776","uuid":"5d8d7637-dfaf-4aca-90b9-a4b7cb8b50c1"}
